1
00:00:03,671 --> 00:00:07,215
Kirk: CAPTAIN'S LOG,
STARDATE 5725.3--

2
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:10,427
THE "ENTERPRISE" IS EN ROUTE
TO MEMORY ALPHA.

3
00:00:10,552 --> 00:00:12,596
IT IS A PLANETOID
SET UP BY THE FEDERATION

4
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:14,932
SOLELY AS A CENTRAL LIBRARY,

5
00:00:15,056 --> 00:00:16,976
CONTAINING THE TOTAL
CULTURAL HISTORY

6
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,477
AND SCIENTIFIC KNOWLEDGE

7
00:00:18,602 --> 00:00:21,647
OF ALL PLANETARY
FEDERATION MEMBERS.

8
00:00:21,772 --> 00:00:24,525
WITH US IS SPECIALIST
LIEUTENANT MIRA ROMAINE.

9
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:26,485
SHE IS ON BOARD
TO SUPERVISE THE TRANSFER

10
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:28,278
OF ALL NEWLY DESIGNED
EQUIPMENT

11
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:31,782
DIRECTLY FROM THE "ENTERPRISE"
TO MEMORY ALPHA.

12
00:00:31,907 --> 00:00:35,285
YOU'RE THE SANEST,
THE SMARTEST,

13
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:39,247
THE NICEST WOMAN
THAT HAS EVER COME
ABOARD THIS SHIP.

14
00:00:39,373 --> 00:00:40,457
ANYTHING ELSE?

15
00:00:42,334 --> 00:00:44,252
ANYTHING ELSE I'LL...

16
00:00:44,378 --> 00:00:47,006
I'LL KEEP TO MYSELF
FOR THE MOMENT.

17
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:50,300
Kirk: WHEN A MAN
OF SCOTTY'S YEARS FALLS IN LOVE,

18
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:53,679
THE LONELINESS OF HIS LIFE
IS SUDDENLY REVEALED TO HIM.

19
00:00:53,804 --> 00:00:57,516
HIS WHOLE HEART ONCE THROBBED
ONLY TO THE SHIP'S ENGINES.

20
00:00:57,641 --> 00:01:00,644
HE COULD TALK
ONLY TO THE SHIP.

21
00:01:00,769 --> 00:01:03,271
NOW HE CAN SEE
NOTHING BUT THE WOMAN.

22
00:01:03,397 --> 00:01:06,817
I DIDN'T THINK
MR. SCOTT WOULD GO
FOR THE BRAINY TYPE.

23
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:09,236
I DON'T THINK HE'S EVEN
NOTICED SHE HAS A BRAIN.

24
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,699
MR. SCOTT.

25
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:17,285
MR. SCOTT.

26
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:19,329
HMM?

27
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:21,957
AS SOON AS WE'RE WITHIN
VIEWING RANGE OF MEMORY ALPHA,

28
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:23,792
YOU AND LIEUTENANT ROMAINE
WILL GO TO YOUR POSITIONS

29
00:01:23,918 --> 00:01:25,210
IN THE EMERGENCY
MANUAL MONITOR.

30
00:01:25,335 --> 00:01:26,712
YOU'LL PREPARE FOR DIRECT
TRANSFER OF EQUIPMENT

31
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:28,672
TO MEMORY ALPHA.

32
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:29,548
AYE, CAPTAIN.

33
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:30,674
WE'RE READY, SIR.

34
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:31,967
Spock: LIEUTENANT,

35
00:01:32,091 --> 00:01:33,677
MAY I OFFER
MY CONGRATULATIONS

36
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,638
ON WHAT WILL BE
YOUR FIRST ASSIGNMENT
FOR THE FEDERATION.

37
00:01:36,764 --> 00:01:37,890
YES. GOOD LUCK,
LIEUTENANT.

38
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:39,098
THANK YOU.

39
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:45,230
[BEEPING]

40
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:46,231
CAPTAIN,
I'M PICKING UP

41
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:47,608
A HIGH INTENSITY
READING.

42
00:01:47,733 --> 00:01:49,777
IS THAT MEMORY ALPHA?

43
00:01:49,902 --> 00:01:50,652
NO, SIR.

44
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:58,493
EXCUSE ME.

45
00:02:01,956 --> 00:02:03,248
MAGNIFICATION 8.

46
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:10,464
WHAT IS THAT?

47
00:02:10,589 --> 00:02:12,424
INDICATIONS
ARE A STORM, CAPTAIN,

48
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:15,135
ALTHOUGH I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE
OF SUCH GREAT INTENSITY

49
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,512
OR STRANGE CONFORMATION.

50
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,139
Kirk: READINGS?

51
00:02:19,264 --> 00:02:21,934
THE SENSOR READINGS ARE
AT MAXIMUM CALIBRATION.

52
00:02:22,059 --> 00:02:23,184
CAPTAIN,
IT'S APPROACHING

53
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,938
AT WARP FACTOR 2.6
AND ACCELERATING.

54
00:02:26,063 --> 00:02:27,689
CHECK THAT.

55
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:28,398
NO NATURAL PHENOMENA
CAN MOVE

56
00:02:28,523 --> 00:02:30,233
FASTER THAN
THE SPEED OF LIGHT.

57
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:33,403
Spock: IT IS DEFINITELY
DOING SO, CAPTAIN.

58
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:36,156
THEREFORE IT CANNOT BE
A PHENOMENON OF NATURE.

59
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,212
DEFLECTORS ON,
CONDITION YELLOW.

60
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:52,380
Uhura: CONDITION
YELLOW, SIR.

61
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:53,799
SHIELDS ACTIVATED,
CAPTAIN.

62
00:02:57,011 --> 00:02:59,680
[NO VOICE]

63
00:03:32,046 --> 00:03:34,882
Kirk: SPACE--
THE FINAL FRONTIER.

64
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:45,184
THESE ARE THE VOYAGES
OF THE STARSHIP "ENTERPRISE."

65
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:49,354
ITS 5-YEAR MISSION--
TO EXPLORE STRANGE NEW WORLDS,

66
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:53,358
TO SEEK OUT NEW LIFE
AND NEW CIVILIZATIONS,

67
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:56,486
TO BOLDLY GO WHERE
NO MAN HAS GONE BEFORE.

68
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:44,868
[NO VOICE]

69
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:00,008
MR. SULU, GET US
THE DEVIL OUT OF HERE!

70
00:05:00,134 --> 00:05:02,636
FULL SCAN ON THE DISTURBANCE
THAT PENETRATED THE BRIDGE.

71
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:05,139
LIEUTENANT, ALL DECKS--
DAMAGE REPORT.

72
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:07,557
MIRA!

73
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,812
Kirk: DR. McCOY, EMERGENCY.
EMERGENCY.

74
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:13,521
MIRA!

75
00:05:18,652 --> 00:05:20,487
[LOW-PITCHED CROAKING]

76
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:22,864
Scotty: WHAT'S THAT
YOU'RE SAYING?

77
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:25,575
[CROAKING]

78
00:05:36,628 --> 00:05:40,299
WAS SHE HURT BY THE FALL
OR THE ACTION OF
THE DISTURBANCE?

79
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,509
I DON'T KNOW.
DID YOU NOTICE, SCOTTY?

80
00:05:42,634 --> 00:05:44,427
WELL, AFTER THE
DISTURBANCE WAS OVER,

81
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:45,971
SHE JUST COLLAPSED.

82
00:05:53,895 --> 00:05:56,023
HOW'S SHE DOING,
DOCTOR?

83
00:05:56,148 --> 00:05:57,858
WELL, I THINK
SHE'S COMING AROUND NOW.

84
00:05:57,983 --> 00:06:00,027
EASY, NOW.

85
00:06:00,152 --> 00:06:02,196
EASY. YOU HAD
QUITE A FALL.

86
00:06:02,321 --> 00:06:05,406
[SIGHS]
I'M--I'M FINE.

87
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:09,786
YOU LET ME BE THE JUDGE
OF THAT.

88
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,205
DO YOU FEEL LIKE WALKING
TO SICK BAY?

89
00:06:11,330 --> 00:06:14,582
I'M FINE, DOCTOR.
REALLY I AM.

90
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:15,625
IS EVERYBODY ELSE
ALL RIGHT?

91
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:16,835
AYE, THEY ARE.

92
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,212
NOW, YOU JUST DO
WHAT DR. McCOY
ORDERED.

93
00:06:18,337 --> 00:06:20,130
WHY? I FEEL
PERFEC--

94
00:06:20,255 --> 00:06:22,007
YOU GET TO
SICK BAY, LIEUTENANT.
THAT'S AN ORDER.

95
00:06:22,132 --> 00:06:23,050
YES, SIR.

96
00:06:23,175 --> 00:06:25,219
CAPTAIN, WOULD IT
BE ALL RIGHT IF I
WENT ALONG TO SICK BAY?

97
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:26,303
NO, MR. SCOTT.
YOU STAY AT YOUR POST,
FOR THE MOMENT.

98
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:27,637
LIEUTENANT UHURA.
CAPTAIN, I--

99
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:28,638
YES, SIR?

100
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:29,348
DAMAGE REPORT.

101
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:31,350
ALL STATIONS
ARE OPERATIVE, SIR.

102
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:32,684
MR. SPOCK.

103
00:06:32,809 --> 00:06:34,311
SOME EQUIPMENT
WAS TEMPORARILY
OUT OF ORDER.

104
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:36,313
MY SENSORS
WERE INOPERATIVE.

105
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:37,981
ANY DAMAGE
TO THE WARP ENGINES?

106
00:06:38,106 --> 00:06:39,566
NONE, CAPTAIN.

107
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,610
GOOD.
FROM THE ACTION
OF THAT...STORM,

108
00:06:42,736 --> 00:06:44,905
WE'LL NEED
ALL THE SPEED
WE CAN GET.

109
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:48,407
CAPTAIN,
IT WAS NOT A STORM.

110
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:49,617
Uhura: CAPTAIN.

111
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:54,956
DURING THE DISTURBANCE,
MEMORY ALPHA WAS HAILING.

112
00:06:55,082 --> 00:06:58,043
I WANTED TO RESPOND,
BUT I COULDN'T MAKE
MY HAND MOVE.

113
00:06:58,168 --> 00:07:01,838
Chekov: CAPTAIN.

114
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:03,422
IT WAS NOT HANDS
THAT WERE PARALYZED.

115
00:07:03,548 --> 00:07:04,758
IT WAS EYES.

116
00:07:04,883 --> 00:07:06,051
I COULD NOT FORCE
MY EYES TO LOOK DOWN

117
00:07:06,176 --> 00:07:07,177
AND SET A NEW COURSE.

118
00:07:07,302 --> 00:07:08,929
Sulu: NO, NO.
IT WAS SPEECH
THAT WAS AFFECTED.

119
00:07:09,054 --> 00:07:10,680
I COULDN'T UTTER
A SOUND.

120
00:07:16,061 --> 00:07:19,147
MR. SPOCK...
EXPLANATION.

121
00:07:19,273 --> 00:07:21,441
ONLY OF THE RESULT,
NOT OF THE CAUSE.

122
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:24,819
IN EACH CASE,
A DIFFERENT AREA OF
THE BRAIN WAS AFFECTED.

123
00:07:24,945 --> 00:07:28,240
OUR VOLUNTARY NERVE
FUNCTIONS WERE UNDER
SOME FORM OF PRESSURE.

124
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:31,618
OR ATTACK.

125
00:07:31,743 --> 00:07:34,621
ATTACK MIGHT BE
A MORE PRECISE
FORMULATION, CAPTAIN.

126
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:43,755
AND LIEUTENANT ROMAINE
SEEMS MOST SUSCEPTIBLE.

127
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,855
ARE THE READINGS
CORRESPONDING, NURSE?

128
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:02,565
EVERYTHING APPEARS
NORMAL, DOCTOR.

129
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:03,524
THANK YOU.

130
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:15,536
WHAT'S THAT
YOU'RE DOING, NURSE?

131
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:18,081
RECORDING YOUR RESPONSES
IN THIS COMPUTER.

132
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:20,500
BUT WHY? I HAVEN'T HAD
A SINGLE RESPONSE WORTH NOTING.

133
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:21,001
LIEUTENANT, PLEASE.

134
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:23,837
WELL, HAVE I?

135
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:27,799
LIEUTENANT,
THERE ARE 430 PEOPLE
ABOARD THIS SHIP.

136
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:30,677
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
THAT PASSED OUT,
AND I WANT TO KNOW WHY.

137
00:08:30,802 --> 00:08:32,387
I WANT TO KNOW WHY, TOO.

138
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:34,222
YOU'RE THE DOCTOR.
YOU TELL ME.

139
00:08:34,348 --> 00:08:35,974
THIS WHOLE THING IS
A NEW EXPERIENCE FOR ME.

140
00:08:36,099 --> 00:08:38,935
THIS WHOLE THING
IS A NEW EXPERIENCE
FOR ALL OF US.

141
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,728
ALL OF YOU ARE ACCUSTOMED
TO NEW EXPERIENCES.

142
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:43,773
IT'S PART OF YOUR WORK.

143
00:08:43,898 --> 00:08:45,525
I'M NOT.

144
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:47,819
SHE MIGHT HAVE
SOMETHING THERE,
DR. McCOY.

145
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,488
THIS IS HER FIRST
DEEP-SPACE TRIP,

146
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,114
AND YOU KNOW HOW
THAT AFFECTS PEOPLE.

147
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,907
WELL, IF WE CAN GET ON
WITH THIS, SCOTTY,

148
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,534
WE MIGHT MAKE
THAT DETERMINATION.

149
00:08:58,038 --> 00:08:59,164
NOW, THEN, TELL ME,

150
00:08:59,289 --> 00:09:02,167
WHAT DID YOU FEEL
BEFORE YOU PASSED OUT?

151
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:03,293
NOTHING.

152
00:09:03,418 --> 00:09:04,752
NOTHING?

153
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:08,006
ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.

154
00:09:08,131 --> 00:09:08,673
LIEUTENANT--

155
00:09:08,798 --> 00:09:11,718
DOCTOR, THERE IS NOTHING
MORE I CAN TELL YOU.

156
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:14,054
LIEUTENANT,
YOU'RE BEING COMPLETELY
UNCOOPERATIVE!

157
00:09:14,179 --> 00:09:16,515
ARE YOU PUTTING THAT
INTO MY RECORD?
IT'S NOT TRUE!

158
00:09:16,639 --> 00:09:19,267
I'LL PUT THE FACTS
INTO YOUR RECORD
IF I CAN GET THEM.

159
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,230
AW, NOW, MIRA,

160
00:09:23,355 --> 00:09:25,190
WE MUST HELP
THE DOCTOR.

161
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,649
TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED.

162
00:09:30,529 --> 00:09:32,739
PERHAPS YOU
CAN EXPLAIN TO HER

163
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:34,949
THAT ANY CAREER SHE
HOPES FOR IN STARFLEET

164
00:09:35,075 --> 00:09:38,953
REQUIRES DISCIPLINE
AND COOPERATION.

165
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,206
WELL, I'M SURE THAT'S WHAT
THE LIEUTENANT WANTS.

166
00:09:41,331 --> 00:09:44,000
SHE JUST DIDN'T UNDERSTAND.

167
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:45,460
DID YOU, NOW, LASS?

168
00:09:49,214 --> 00:09:51,341
WITH A BEDSIDE MANNER
LIKE THAT, SCOTTY,

169
00:09:51,466 --> 00:09:53,301
YOU'RE IN
THE WRONG BUSINESS.

170
00:09:58,515 --> 00:09:59,849
WHEN THE RECORD
OF THIS IS FORWARDED,

171
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,268
I'LL BE SENT BACK,
WON'T I?

172
00:10:01,393 --> 00:10:04,396
OH, YOU WILL NOT!
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

173
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,189
THIS GETTING USED
TO SPACE TRAVEL,

174
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:07,857
THAT TAKES SOME DOING.

175
00:10:07,982 --> 00:10:09,359
AND NOT EVERYBODY
TAKES TO IT.

176
00:10:09,484 --> 00:10:11,152
DID YOU?

177
00:10:11,278 --> 00:10:13,321
WELL, ME,
THAT'S DIFFERENT.

178
00:10:13,447 --> 00:10:15,156
I WAS PRACTICALLY
BORN TO IT.

179
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:18,076
I WANT TO CONTINUE.

180
00:10:18,201 --> 00:10:19,660
YOU WILL.

181
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:21,288
YOU PASSED
YOUR STARFLEET

182
00:10:21,413 --> 00:10:25,625
PRELIMINARY
EXAMINATIONS.

183
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,835
AND THIS IS
JUST GETTING USED

184
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:30,713
TO WHAT YOU MIGHT CALL
YOUR SPACE LEGS.

185
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:37,845
I HOPE THAT'S
ALL IT IS.

186
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:40,515
CAPTAIN, I'VE PLOTTED
THE STORM'S PATH.

187
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,016
MR. LEMLI.

188
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,229
MAIN SCREEN
PROJECTION.

189
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:50,150
Sulu: ON
ITS PRESENT COURSE,

190
00:10:50,275 --> 00:10:53,236
IT WILL HIT THE MEMORY ALPHA
PLANETOID AS IT DID US.

191
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:55,530
LIEUTENANT, TRY
AND WARN MEMORY ALPHA

192
00:10:55,655 --> 00:10:57,240
OF THE PROXIMITY
OF THAT PHENOMENON.

193
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:59,326
GIVE ME AN E.T.A.
FOR ITS POSSIBLE IMPACT.

194
00:10:59,451 --> 00:11:03,037
I CANNOT, SIR.
IT HAS THE ABILITY
TO CHANGE SPEED.

195
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:05,624
SIR, I'M UNABLE TO ESTABLISH
CONTACT WITH THE PLANETOID.

196
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:08,543
I'M HAILING ON ALL
FREQUENCIES. NO RESPONSE.

197
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,670
IT IS OF LITTLE
CONSEQUENCE, CAPTAIN.

198
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:13,256
MEMORY ALPHA HAS
NO PROTECTIVE SHIELDS.

199
00:11:13,381 --> 00:11:14,466
NO SHIELDS?

200
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:15,674
NONE, CAPTAIN.

201
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,760
WHEN THE LIBRARY COMPLEX
WAS ASSEMBLED,

202
00:11:17,885 --> 00:11:19,387
SHIELDING WAS
CONSIDERED INAPPROPRIATE

203
00:11:19,513 --> 00:11:21,473
TO ITS TOTALLY
ACADEMIC PURPOSE.

204
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:23,183
SINCE THE INFORMATION
ON THE MEMORY PLANET

205
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:25,185
IS FREELY AVAILABLE
TO EVERYONE,

206
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:27,728
SPECIAL PROTECTION
WAS DEEMED UNNECESSARY.

207
00:11:27,854 --> 00:11:29,439
WONDERFUL.

208
00:11:29,564 --> 00:11:32,108
I HOPE THE STORM IS AWARE
OF THAT RATIONALE.

209
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:34,152
COMPLETING APPROACH
TO PLANETOID.

210
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:36,488
IT IS ALREADY OVER
MEMORY ALPHA,
CAPTAIN.

211
00:11:36,613 --> 00:11:38,281
ITS SPEED
IS INCREDIBLE.

212
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:39,616
IT'S HITTING
THE PLANETOID.

213
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,621
Kirk: ARE WE WITHIN
ORBIT RANGE, MR. CHEKOV?

214
00:11:44,745 --> 00:11:46,122
MAKING FINAL APPROACH.

215
00:11:46,247 --> 00:11:47,582
LIEUTENANT,
TRY AND WARN THEM--

216
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:50,126
I'M SORRY, SIR.
I CAN'T BREAK THROUGH
THIS INTERFERENCE.

217
00:11:56,841 --> 00:12:02,096
MR. SPOCK,
HOW MANY PEOPLE
ARE ON MEMORY ALPHA?

218
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:05,141
IT VARIES WITH THE NUMBER
OF SCHOLARS, RESEARCHERS,
AND SCIENTISTS

219
00:12:05,266 --> 00:12:06,767
FROM VARIOUS
FEDERATION PLANETS

220
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:08,895
WHO ARE USING
THE COMPUTER COMPLEX.

221
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,523
Chekov: CAPTAIN,
WE ARE WITHIN
ORBIT RANGE.

222
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:17,778
LOCK INTO ORBIT.

223
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:18,655
Chekov:
AYE, SIR.

224
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:21,157
Sulu: IT IS LEAVING
MEMORY ALPHA,
CAPTAIN.

225
00:12:21,282 --> 00:12:23,159
Spock: SENSORS GIVE NO READINGS
OF GENERATED ENERGY

226
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:24,994
FROM MEMORY ALPHA,
CAPTAIN.

227
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:26,787
ANY LIFE READINGS?

228
00:12:26,913 --> 00:12:27,664
NONE.

229
00:12:32,711 --> 00:12:35,338
LET'S FIND OUT WHAT'S
GOING ON DOWN THERE.

230
00:12:38,675 --> 00:12:40,968
KIRK TO ENGINEERING.
MR. SCOTT, REPORT.

231
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:43,971
KIRK TO ENGINEERING.
MR. SCOTT!

232
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:45,890
WHERE THE DEVIL IS HE?

233
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:49,436
SCOTTY, REPORT TO THE BRIDGE.
REPORT TO THE BRIDGE.

234
00:12:49,561 --> 00:12:51,187
HAVE THE TRANSPORTER ROOM
STAND BY.

235
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:52,564
I'M TAKING A LANDING PARTY
DOWN THERE.

236
00:12:52,689 --> 00:12:53,022
Uhura:
AYE, AYE, SIR.

237
00:12:53,147 --> 00:12:55,692
SCOTT HERE.

238
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:57,944
SCOTTY,
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?
WHERE ARE YOU?

239
00:12:58,069 --> 00:12:59,320
IN THE SICK BAY.

240
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:00,488
ARE YOU SICK?

241
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:04,701
OH, NO. I WAS JUST
CHECKING ON THE LASS.

242
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:05,452
SHE'S GOING TO BE FINE NOW.

243
00:13:05,577 --> 00:13:06,911
THERE'S NOTHING
WRONG WITH HER.

244
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:10,039
WELL, I'M RELIEVED TO HEAR
YOUR PROGNOSIS, MR. SCOTT.

245
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:12,709
IS THE DOCTOR THERE
WITH YOU, OR WILL I
FIND HIM IN ENGINEERING?

246
00:13:15,128 --> 00:13:17,380
McCOY HERE, JIM.

247
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,757
DOCTOR,
HOW'S THE GIRL?

248
00:13:18,881 --> 00:13:20,341
I THINK
SHE'S IN GOOD SHAPE.

249
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:23,094
Kirk: WELL, MR. SCOTT
SEEMS TO AGREE WITH YOU.

250
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:24,095
THE TWO OF YOU
MEET ME

251
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,013
IN THE TRANSPORTER
ROOM ON THE DOUBLE.

252
00:13:45,492 --> 00:13:48,411
Kirk: CAPTAIN'S LOG,
SUPPLEMENTAL,

253
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:52,039
STARDATE 5725.6--

254
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:54,292
THE STORM HAS CLEARED
MEMORY ALPHA.

255
00:13:54,417 --> 00:13:57,295
IT IS HEADING AWAY
AT INCREDIBLE SPEED.

256
00:13:57,420 --> 00:14:00,548
WE HAVE BEEN UNABLE TO MAKE
CONTACT WITH THE PLANETOID.

257
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:03,468
ITS SILENCE IS OMINOUS.

258
00:14:03,593 --> 00:14:05,928
WE ARE BEAMING DOWN
TO INVESTIGATE.

259
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:09,182
SOMEHOW I FIND

260
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:11,601
TRANSPORTING
INTO THE DARKNESS
UNNERVING.

261
00:14:11,726 --> 00:14:12,602
SCOTTY, CAN YOU
GIVE US SOME MORE LIGHT?

262
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:24,489
I'M AFRAID THIS LIGHT
WILL HAVE TO DO, CAPTAIN.

263
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:26,157
THE GENERATOR
IS INOPERATIVE.

264
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,034
DAMAGE REPORT,
SPOCK.

265
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:29,828
A DISASTER FOR
THE GALAXY, CAPTAIN.

266
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,162
THE CENTRAL BRAIN
IS DAMAGED.

267
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:32,497
THE MEMORY CORE
IS BURNT OUT.

268
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:35,124
THE LOSS TO THE GALAXY
MAY BE IRRETRIEVABLE.

269
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,877
CAPTAIN!

270
00:15:02,485 --> 00:15:03,862
A VERY FAINT
LIFE READING

271
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,697
IN THE IMMEDIATE
VICINITY, CAPTAIN.

272
00:15:05,822 --> 00:15:06,656
LOCATE THEM.
KEEP THEM ALIVE.

273
00:15:06,781 --> 00:15:09,367
WE NEED MORE INFORMATION
ABOUT THIS ENEMY.

274
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:13,621
OVER HERE, CAPTAIN.

275
00:15:19,502 --> 00:15:21,588
[LOW-PITCHED CROAKING]

276
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:27,343
BONES, CAN YOU
DO SOMETHING?

277
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:28,553
NOT A THING, JIM.

278
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:34,809
[CROAKING]

279
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:38,187
IT'S THE SAME
GARBLED SOUNDS
LIEUTENANT ROMAINE MADE

280
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:39,647
WHEN SHE FAINTED
AFTER THE STORM.

281
00:15:39,773 --> 00:15:40,648
ARE YOU SURE?

282
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:42,066
ABSOLUTELY SURE.

283
00:15:44,026 --> 00:15:44,944
KIRK TO
"ENTERPRISE."

284
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:45,612
SULU HERE.

285
00:15:45,737 --> 00:15:47,864
BEAM DOWN
LIEUTENANT ROMAINE
IMMEDIATELY.

286
00:15:47,988 --> 00:15:49,073
YES, SIR.

287
00:15:50,742 --> 00:15:52,577
[CROAKING]

288
00:15:58,458 --> 00:16:01,461
SPOCK...

289
00:16:01,586 --> 00:16:02,879
HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
ANYTHING LIKE
THAT BEFORE?

290
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:03,880
NEGATIVE.

291
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:06,633
[CROAKING]

292
00:16:10,595 --> 00:16:11,805
[SILENT]

293
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:13,890
BONES?

294
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:15,767
SHE'S DEAD.

295
00:16:15,892 --> 00:16:17,602
WHAT DID SHE
DIE OF?

296
00:16:17,727 --> 00:16:19,103
SEVERE BRAIN HEMORRHAGING

297
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,731
DUE TO DISTORTION OF
ALL NEURAL SYSTEMS,

298
00:16:21,856 --> 00:16:24,567
DISSOLUTION OF AUTONOMIC
NERVOUS SYSTEM,

299
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:27,361
ALL BASIC PERSONALITY
FACTORS, CAPTAIN.

300
00:16:27,487 --> 00:16:30,239
THE ATTACK
WAS THOROUGH.

301
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:32,158
WHAT DID THE OTHERS
DIE OF?

302
00:16:32,283 --> 00:16:33,952
EACH HAD A DIFFERENT
CENTER OF BRAIN DESTROYED,

303
00:16:34,076 --> 00:16:35,745
CAUSE UNKNOWN.

304
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:38,498
A DIFFERENT CENTER
OF THE BRAIN, YOU SAY?

305
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:41,292
YES, CAPTAIN.
I CAN BE MORE DETAILED

306
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,544
WHEN WE RETURN TO THE SHIP
AND USE THE SHIP'S COMPUTERS.

307
00:16:49,592 --> 00:16:50,927
Scotty: MIRA!

308
00:16:52,428 --> 00:16:54,263
THE CAPTAIN
HAS SOME QUESTIONS.

309
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:57,517
YES, CAPTAIN?

310
00:16:57,642 --> 00:17:00,979
LIEUTENANT, WHEN YOU
WERE UNCONSCIOUS,
YOU WERE...SPEAKING.

311
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:02,856
WHAT DID I SAY?

312
00:17:02,981 --> 00:17:05,232
I DON'T KNOW.
THE WORDS WERE
UNFAMILIAR TO ME.

313
00:17:05,358 --> 00:17:06,985
WHAT DID IT
SOUND LIKE?

314
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:08,277
THEY SOUNDED
EXACTLY LIKE

315
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:09,988
THE LAST WORDS SPOKEN
BY THE TECHNICIAN.

316
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:12,072
WHAT TECHNICIAN?

317
00:17:12,198 --> 00:17:14,492
WE FOUND ONE PERSON IN THERE
JUST BARELY ALIVE.

318
00:17:14,617 --> 00:17:17,036
THE REST WERE DEAD,
AND WE--

319
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:18,245
LIEUTENANT.

320
00:17:26,671 --> 00:17:28,172
LIEUTENANT.

321
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:30,008
WE MUST GET BACK
TO THE SHIP!

322
00:17:30,132 --> 00:17:32,343
WHY? TELL ME WHY.

323
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:35,137
THAT STORM--
IT'S RETURNING.

324
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:36,305
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

325
00:17:36,430 --> 00:17:39,392
I KNOW.
YOU'LL BE KILLED IF WE STAY.

326
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:41,561
Spock: LIEUTENANT,
I ASSURE YOU,

327
00:17:41,686 --> 00:17:44,647
THAT UNEXPLAINED
PHENOMENON WAS HEADED
AWAY FROM THE PLANET.

328
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,607
IT IS PROBABLY SEEKING
OTHER VICTIMS.

329
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,442
I TELL YOU,
IT WILL KILL US.

330
00:17:54,532 --> 00:17:56,450
"ENTERPRISE" TO CAPTAIN KIRK.

331
00:17:56,576 --> 00:17:58,202
KIRK HERE.
Sulu: BRIDGE, SIR.

332
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:01,539
THE STORM HAS REAPPEARED
ON THE LONG-RANGE SCANNER
AND IS CLOSING FAST.

333
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:07,169
WHAT'S ITS COURSE?

334
00:18:07,294 --> 00:18:08,755
COMING BACK
IN THIS DIRECTION.

335
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:12,675
BEAM US UP.

336
00:18:23,978 --> 00:18:25,187
MR. SULU, THIS IS
THE CAPTAIN.

337
00:18:25,312 --> 00:18:26,564
GET THE "ENTERPRISE"
OUT OF HERE.

338
00:18:26,689 --> 00:18:28,274
WAIT, CAPTAIN!
WE'VE LOST MIRA.

339
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,736
BELAY THAT ORDER,
MR. SULU.

340
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:33,195
STABILIZER.

341
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,530
SOMETHING'S INTERFERING WITH
THE TRANSPORTER SIGNAL.

342
00:18:34,655 --> 00:18:36,824
I HAVE HER COORDINATES,
BUT SHE'S SUSPENDED IN TRANSIT.

343
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:38,534
LET ME.

344
00:19:02,809 --> 00:19:05,853
Kirk: ALL RIGHT, MR. SULU,
GET US OUT OF HERE.

345
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:08,856
MR. SCOTT, CHECK
EMERGENCY MANUAL MONITOR
FOR TRANSPORTER CONTROL.

346
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:26,248
CAPTAIN, IT'S
CHANGING COURSE.

347
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,002
PLOT THE NEW COURSE,
MR. CHEKOV.

348
00:19:29,127 --> 00:19:31,420
PRESENT COURSE
IS 126 MARK 20.

349
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:32,296
PLOT IT.

350
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:33,923
PRESENT COURSE
WILL BRING IT

351
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,258
ACROSS OUR STARBOARD
SIDE, SIR.

352
00:19:36,383 --> 00:19:37,927
MR. SPOCK, YOU MADE
A STATEMENT

353
00:19:38,052 --> 00:19:40,805
THAT PHENOMENON
IS NOT A STORM.

354
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:42,306
EXPLAIN IT.

355
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:43,891
NO KNOWN CONDITIONS IN SPACE

356
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:45,977
WOULD SUPPORT THAT TYPE
OF NATURAL PHENOMENON.

357
00:19:46,102 --> 00:19:46,811
WHAT IS IT?

358
00:19:46,936 --> 00:19:47,937
CAPTAIN, I'M
HAVING DIFFICULTY

359
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:48,980
WITH THE SHIP'S SENSORS.

360
00:19:49,105 --> 00:19:51,774
THEY SEEM TO BE
UNDER SELECTIVE ATTACK
BY THE PHENOMENON

361
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:55,153
AS THE UNFORTUNATE OCCUPANTS
OF MEMORY ALPHA WERE.

362
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:58,322
THEN DEDUCTIVE
REASONING WILL HAVE
TO BE SUBSTITUTED.

363
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:01,117
Spock: SHIP'S SENSORS ARE
OPERATING AT THE MOMENT.

364
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:04,954
PERHAPS THE ELUSIVE
CREATURE WILL NOW REVEAL
SOMETHING ABOUT ITSELF.

365
00:20:05,079 --> 00:20:07,247
BUT I SAW
THOSE MEN DEAD...

366
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:09,333
IN THEIR EXACT
POSITIONS.

367
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:11,377
LISTEN TO ME.

368
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:13,295
I'VE TOLD YOU
WHAT STRANGE TRICKS

369
00:20:13,420 --> 00:20:15,173
A SPACE TRIP CAN
PLAY ON YOUR MIND.

370
00:20:15,297 --> 00:20:17,008
NOW, THAT'S ALL IT IS.

371
00:20:17,133 --> 00:20:18,843
NO, SCOTTY.

372
00:20:20,094 --> 00:20:23,806
HAVE YOU EVER HAD VISIONS
OF THE FUTURE EVENTS
BEFORE THIS?

373
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:25,558
NEVER.

374
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:27,894
WELL, IF YOU ASK ME,
NOBODY EVER HAS.

375
00:20:28,019 --> 00:20:30,188
THAT SEEING OF THE FUTURE--
IT'S PURE BUNK.

376
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:32,857
YOU KNOW THAT,
DON'T YOU?

377
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:34,150
I'VE ALWAYS
BELIEVED IT.

378
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:35,860
AND YOU WERE
PERFECTLY RIGHT.

379
00:20:38,529 --> 00:20:39,989
THEN WHAT IS IT, SCOTTY?

380
00:20:40,114 --> 00:20:41,281
WHAT'S FRIGHTENING ME?

381
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,534
EVER SINCE THAT...
THAT STORM HIT,

382
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:45,411
I'VE...I'VE HAD
SUCH STRANGE THOUGHTS,

383
00:20:45,536 --> 00:20:49,123
SUCH FEELINGS OF...
OF TERROR.

384
00:20:49,248 --> 00:20:51,709
SPACE.

385
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:55,004
SPACE--
THAT'S ALL IT IS.

386
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,967
THEN I DON'T HAVE
TO REPORT IT?

387
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:03,512
IF YOU WANT TO SPEND
THE REST OF THE TRIP
IN SICK BAY.

388
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:04,764
BUT WHAT GOOD
WOULD THAT DO?

389
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:07,975
DR. McCOY CAN
NO MORE CURE IT
THAN HE CAN A COLD.

390
00:21:15,649 --> 00:21:18,027
CAPTAIN, IT'S HEADING
STRAIGHT FOR US.

391
00:21:18,152 --> 00:21:19,612
ACTIVATE SHIELDS.

392
00:21:19,737 --> 00:21:21,530
SHIELDS ACTIVATED.

393
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:24,825
MR. CHEKOV, CHANGE COURSE
TO ONE 4 3 MARK 3

394
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:26,744
ONE 4 3 MARK 3.

395
00:21:26,869 --> 00:21:28,788
STORM'S COURSE, MR. SULU?

396
00:21:28,913 --> 00:21:30,539
ONE 4 3 MARK 3.

397
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:33,209
TAKE EVASIVE ACTION.

398
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,586
Sulu:
EVASIVE ACTION.

399
00:21:35,711 --> 00:21:39,506
HARD STARBOARD,
2 ONE 7 MARK 5.

400
00:21:39,632 --> 00:21:41,592
2 ONE 7 MARK 5.

401
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:58,776
Sulu: STILL
WITH US, SIR.

402
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:00,861
HARD PORT.

403
00:22:00,987 --> 00:22:04,490
117 MARK 2.

404
00:22:04,615 --> 00:22:06,700
117 MARK 2.

405
00:22:10,163 --> 00:22:11,580
Sulu:
STILL WITH US, SIR.

406
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,835
IS IT CLOSING?

407
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,378
Spock: NEGATIVE, CAPTAIN.
MAINTAINING ITS DISTANCE.

408
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:21,799
HOWEVER, IT IS MATCHING
EACH MANEUVER WE EXECUTE,

409
00:22:21,924 --> 00:22:25,970
AND I AM RECEIVING INCREASING
MAGNITUDE OF ENERGY.

410
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:51,912
YOUR ANALYSIS, SPOCK.

411
00:22:52,038 --> 00:22:53,206
WHAT IS IT?

412
00:22:53,331 --> 00:22:55,208
NOT WHAT IS "IT,"
CAPTAIN.

413
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:56,625
WHAT ARE "THEY"?

414
00:22:59,045 --> 00:23:01,463
THERE ARE 10 DISTINCT
LIFE UNITS WITHIN IT,

415
00:23:01,588 --> 00:23:03,799
ALL POWERFULLY ALIVE
AND VITAL.

416
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,095
Kirk: WHO ARE THEY?
WHERE ARE THEY FROM?

417
00:23:08,221 --> 00:23:10,348
IMPOSSIBLE TO DETERMINE
WITHOUT PROGRAMMING

418
00:23:10,472 --> 00:23:11,557
FOR COMPUTER ANALYSIS.

419
00:23:11,682 --> 00:23:12,975
IT'S CLEAR WE CAN'T
OUTRUN THEM.

420
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:14,352
CAN WE SHIELD
AGAINST THEM?

421
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,145
I DO NOT BELIEVE
THE "ENTERPRISE" SHIELDS

422
00:23:16,270 --> 00:23:17,521
WOULD PROVE
AN EFFECTIVE DEFENSE.

423
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:20,149
THERE MUST BE SOME
DEFENSE WE CAN USE.

424
00:23:20,274 --> 00:23:23,194
CAPTAIN, WE ARE DEALING
WITH A COMMUNITY
OF LIFE UNITS.

425
00:23:23,319 --> 00:23:25,905
THEIR ATTACK IS IN
THE FORM OF BRAIN WAVES

426
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:29,325
DIRECTED AGAINST
THE BRAIN WHICH IS
MOST COMPATIBLE.

427
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:31,327
MAYBE WE CAN AVOID
ANOTHER ATTACK.

428
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:33,411
LIEUTENANT UHURA,
OPEN ALL CHANNELS,

429
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:35,539
TIE IN THE UNIVERSAL
TRANSLATOR.

430
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:37,666
MR. SPOCK SAYS IT'S ALIVE.

431
00:23:39,710 --> 00:23:41,962
MAYBE I CAN TALK TO IT.

432
00:23:42,088 --> 00:23:44,506
Uhura: ALL CHANNELS OPEN,
TRANSLATOR TIED IN.

433
00:23:49,636 --> 00:23:50,888
THIS IS CAPTAIN
JAMES KIRK

434
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:53,224
OF THE U.S.S.
"ENTERPRISE."

435
00:23:53,349 --> 00:23:54,808
WE WISH YOU
NO HARM.

436
00:24:08,739 --> 00:24:09,990
PHYSICAL CONTACT
BETWEEN US

437
00:24:10,116 --> 00:24:11,617
IS FATAL TO
OUR LIFE FORMS.

438
00:24:11,742 --> 00:24:15,162
PLEASE, DO NOT
COME ANY CLOSER
TO OUR SHIP.

439
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:21,627
PERHAPS IT DID NOT
UNDERSTAND.

440
00:24:21,752 --> 00:24:24,671
Sulu: CAPTAIN,
CHANGE IN VELOCITY
RECORDED.

441
00:24:27,425 --> 00:24:28,884
Sulu: THEY
ARE PASSING
OUR STARBOARD SIDE

442
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,386
AND MANEUVERING
IN FRONT OF US.

443
00:24:30,510 --> 00:24:32,554
SWITCHING
TO FORWARD SCANNER.

444
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:45,525
CAPTAIN, CHANGE
IN VELOCITY RECORDED.

445
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:47,569
IT HAS ACCELERATED
ITS APPROACH.

446
00:24:53,326 --> 00:24:55,328
HELP, SCOTTY.

447
00:24:55,453 --> 00:24:57,621
HELP. HOLD ME!

448
00:24:57,746 --> 00:24:59,081
IT'S HAPPENING
AGAIN!

449
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:08,257
NO!

450
00:25:08,382 --> 00:25:09,716
MIRA.

451
00:25:12,803 --> 00:25:16,849
PERHAPS IT
UNDERSTANDS ANOTHER
KIND OF LANGUAGE.

452
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:17,850
CONDITION RED ALERT.

453
00:25:17,975 --> 00:25:19,268
[ALARM SOUNDING]

454
00:25:19,393 --> 00:25:21,103
PREPARE FOR
PHASER FIRING.

455
00:25:22,438 --> 00:25:23,981
MIRA.

456
00:25:24,106 --> 00:25:26,442
NO, SCOTTY! NO!

457
00:25:26,566 --> 00:25:28,319
NO.

458
00:25:28,444 --> 00:25:31,030
Kirk: LOCK IN PHASER
TRACKING CONTROLS.

459
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:33,531
LOCKED IN, SIR.

460
00:25:33,657 --> 00:25:36,452
ADJUST PHASERS TO FIRE
